  "summary": "The 4-Week Treasury Bill Secondary Market Rate (DTB4WK) is tightly anchored to the Federal Funds rate, currently at the 3.5%-3.75% target range (effective rate 3.64%). The Fed held rates steady at its March 18, 2026 meeting, and the next FOMC meeting isn't until April 29 — well after the April 9 resolution date. Rate futures imply 3.64% through May 2026 with no expected change. Over the last 30 trading days, the rate has oscillated narrowly between 3.62-3.65, with 80% of observations at 3.63 or 3.64. A bootstrap Monte Carlo simulation using stable-regime daily changes produces a very tight distribution centered at 3.63. The only risk is an extreme geopolitical shock (Iran war context mentioned by the Fed), but 4-week bills are too short-dated for this to meaningfully decouple from the Fed funds rate.",
